The paper discusses SimuLTE, a tool for simulating LTE/LTE-Advanced networks within OMNeT++. The focus of the paper is on simulating device-to-device (D2D) communications, which is a topic of interest in several research fields, including vehicular networks, IoT, and M2M applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely categories include cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
